681 #ifdef WITH_C_LOCALE
682 # include <locale.h>
683 # if defined(WIN32) && !defined(CYGWIN)
684 # define SOAP_LOCALE_T _locale_t
685 # define SOAP_LOCALE(soap) ((soap)->c_locale ? (soap)->c_locale : ((soap)->c_locale = _create_locale(LC_ALL, "C")))
686 # define SOAP_FREELOCALE(soap) (void)((soap)->c_locale && (_free_locale((soap)->c_locale), ((soap)->c_locale = NULL)))
687 # else
688 # if defined(HAVE_XLOCALE_H)
689 # include <xlocale.h>

1270 /* SOAP_MAXARRAYSIZE: Trusted total max size of an inbound SOAP Array.
1271  Arrays of larger size are not pre-allocated, but deserialized
1272  on an element-by-element basis until XML validation contrains kick in.
1273  This macro only affects the efficiency of parsing SOAP arrays.
1274 */
1275 #ifndef SOAP_MAXARRAYSIZE
1276 # define SOAP_MAXARRAYSIZE (100000)
1277 #endif
1278 
1279 /* SOAP_MAXDIMESIZE: Trusted max size of inbound DIME data.
1280  Increase if necessary to allow larger attachments, or decrease when server
1281  resources are limited. This is to deny senders to allocate more than 8 MB
1282  at the receiver without actually sending the whole message.
1283 */
1284 #ifndef SOAP_MAXDIMESIZE
1285 # define SOAP_MAXDIMESIZE (8*1048576) /* 8 MB */
1286 #endif
1287 
1288 /* SOAP_MAXINFLATESIZE: Trusted inflated content size.
1289  Larger content is subject to the SOAP_MINDEFLATERATIO constraint.
1290  If SOAP_MINDEFLATERATIO is 1.0, SOAP_MAXINFLATESIZE is always the max
1291  size of uncompressed content.
1292 */
1293 #ifndef SOAP_MAXINFLATESIZE
1294 # define SOAP_MAXINFLATESIZE (1*1048576) /* 1 MB */
1295 #endif
1296 
1297 /* SOAP_MINDEFLATERATIO: Trusted deflation ratio after SOAP_MAXINFLATESIZE is reached.
1298  Trust when compressed / deflated > SOAP_MINDEFLATERATIO
1299  Sets a ratio > 0.00096899224806 (1032:1)
1300  According to the zlib site: the limit (1032:1) comes from the fact that one
1301  length/distance pair can represent at most 258 output bytes. A length
1302  requires at least one bit and a distance requires at least one bit, so two
1303  bits in can give 258 bytes out, or eight bits in give 1032 bytes out. A
1304  dynamic block has no length restriction, so you could get arbitrarily close
1305  to the limit of 1032:1.
1306 */
1307 #ifndef SOAP_MINDEFLATERATIO
1308 # define SOAP_MINDEFLATERATIO (1.0/1032.0) /* ratio of deflated/inflated */
1309 #endif
1310 
1311 /* maximum XML nesting depth level allowed for inbound XML parsing, must be greater than zero (0) */
1312 #ifndef SOAP_MAXLEVEL
1313 # define SOAP_MAXLEVEL (10000)
1314 #endif
1315 
1316 /* maximum string content length if not already constrained by XML schema validation maxLength constraints, zero or negative means unlimited string lengths are allowed unless restricted by XML schema maxLength */

1456 /* Safer str & mem functions */
1457 
1458 /* The gSOAP code uses guards to ensure that these functions are well behaved
1459  and do not raise errors. Therefore, the WIN _s functions should never
1460  execute the "invalid parameter handler".
1461 */
1462 
1463 /* use safer snprintf if possible or guard sprintf against overrun (assumes no variadic macros) */
1464 # ifdef HAVE_SNPRINTF
1465 # if _MSC_VER >= 1400
1466 # define SOAP_SNPRINTF(buf, len, num) void)_snprintf_s((buf), (len), _TRUNCATE
1467 # define SOAP_SNPRINTF_SAFE(buf, len) void)_snprintf_s((buf), (len), _TRUNCATE
1468 # else
1469 # define SOAP_SNPRINTF(buf, len, num) void)snprintf((buf), (len)
1470 # define SOAP_SNPRINTF_SAFE(buf, len) void)snprintf((buf), (len)
1471 # endif
1472 # else
1473 # define SOAP_SNPRINTF(buf, len, num) (len) <= (num)) ? (void)((buf)[0] = '\0') : (void)sprintf((buf)
1474 # define SOAP_SNPRINTF_SAFE(buf, len) void)sprintf((buf)
1475 # endif
1476 
1477 /* copy string (truncating the result, strings must not be NULL) */
1478 #if _MSC_VER >= 1400
1479 # define soap_strcpy(buf, len, src) (void)strncpy_s((buf), (len), (src), _TRUNCATE)
1480 #elif defined(HAVE_STRLCPY)
1481 # define soap_strcpy(buf, len, src) (void)strlcpy((buf), (src), (len))
1482 #else
1483 # define soap_strcpy(buf, len, src) (void)(strncpy((buf), (src), (len)), (buf)[(len) - 1] = '\0')
1484 #endif
1485 
1486 /* concat string (truncating the result, strings must not be NULL) */
1487 #if _MSC_VER >= 1400
1488 # define soap_strcat(buf, len, src) (void)strncat_s((buf), (len), (src), _TRUNCATE)
1489 #elif defined(HAVE_STRLCAT)
1490 # define soap_strcat(buf, len, src) (void)strlcat((buf), (src), (len))
1491 #else
1492 SOAP_FMAC1 void SOAP_FMAC2 soap_strcat(char *buf, size_t len, const char *src);
1493 #endif
1494 
1495 /* copy string up to num chars (sets string to empty on overrun and returns nonzero, zero if OK) */
1496 #if _MSC_VER >= 1400
1497 # define soap_strncpy(buf, len, src, num) ((buf) == NULL || ((size_t)(len) > (size_t)(num) ? strncpy_s((buf), (len), (src), (num)) : ((buf)[0] = '\0', 1)))
1498 #else
1499 # define soap_strncpy(buf, len, src, num) ((buf) == NULL || ((size_t)(len) > (size_t)(num) ? (strncpy((buf), (src), (num)), (buf)[(size_t)(num)] = '\0') : ((buf)[0] = '\0', 1)))
1500 #endif
1501 
1502 /* concat string up to n chars (leaves destination intact on overrun and returns nonzero, zero if OK) */
1503 #if _MSC_VER >= 1400
1504 # define soap_strncat(buf, len, src, num) ((buf) == NULL || ((size_t)(len) > strlen((buf)) + (size_t)(num) ? strncat_s((buf), (len), (src), (num)) : 1))
1505 #else
1506 SOAP_FMAC1 int SOAP_FMAC2 soap_strncat(char *buf, size_t len, const char *src, size_t num);
1507 #endif
1508 
1509 /* copy memory (returns SOAP_ERANGE on overrun, zero if OK, pointers must not be NULL) */
1510 #if _MSC_VER >= 1400
1511 # define soap_memcpy(buf, len, src, num) ((size_t)(len) >= (size_t)(num) ? memcpy_s((buf), (len), (src), (num)) : SOAP_ERANGE)
1512 #else
1513 # define soap_memcpy(buf, len, src, num) ((size_t)(len) >= (size_t)(num) ? !memcpy((buf), (src), (num)) : SOAP_ERANGE)
1514 #endif
1515 
1516 /* move memory (returns SOAP_ERANGE on overrun, zero if OK, pointers must not be NULL) */
1517 #if _MSC_VER >= 1400
1518 # define soap_memmove(buf, len, src, num) ((size_t)(len) >= (size_t)(num) ? memmove_s((buf), (len), (src), (num)) : SOAP_ERANGE)
1519 #else
1520 # define soap_memmove(buf, len, src, num) ((size_t)(len) >= (size_t)(num) ? !memmove((buf), (src), (num)) : SOAP_ERANGE)
1521 #endif

1691 #define SOAP_IO_BUFFER 0x00000001 /* out: buffer output in packets of size SOAP_BUFLEN */
1692 #define SOAP_IO_STORE 0x00000002 /* out: store entire output to determine length for transport */

1836 # if defined(__GNUC__) && (__GNUC__ <= 2)
1837 # define SOAP_NOTHROW
1838 # elif defined(WITH_LEAN) || defined(WITH_COMPAT)
1839 # define SOAP_NOTHROW

1845 #if defined(__BORLANDC__) && !defined(__clang__)
1846 /* Embarcadero Classic compiler special case */
1847 # ifndef SOAP_NEW
1848 # define SOAP_NEW(soap, type) new SOAP_NOTHROW (type)
1849 # endif
1850 # ifndef SOAP_NEW_ARRAY
1851 # define SOAP_NEW_ARRAY(soap, type, n) new SOAP_NOTHROW (type[n])
1852 # endif
1853 # ifndef SOAP_PLACEMENT_NEW
1854 # define SOAP_PLACEMENT_NEW(soap, buf, type) new (buf) (type)
1855 # endif
1856 #elif (defined(__GNUC__) && (__GNUC__ <= 2)) || defined(__clang__) || defined(_AIX) || defined(AIX)
1857 /* old form w/o parenthesis, soap context may be NULL */
1858 # ifndef SOAP_NEW
1859 # define SOAP_NEW(soap, type) new SOAP_NOTHROW type
1860 # endif
1861 # ifndef SOAP_NEW_ARRAY
1862 # define SOAP_NEW_ARRAY(soap, type, n) new SOAP_NOTHROW type[n]
1863 # endif
1864 # ifndef SOAP_PLACEMENT_NEW
1865 # define SOAP_PLACEMENT_NEW(soap, buf, type) new (buf) type
1866 # endif
1867 #else
1868 /* new form with parenthesis for (type) but not type[n], soap context may be NULL */
1869 # ifndef SOAP_NEW
1870 # define SOAP_NEW(soap, type) new SOAP_NOTHROW (type)
1871 # endif
1872 # ifndef SOAP_NEW_ARRAY
1873 # define SOAP_NEW_ARRAY(soap, type, n) new SOAP_NOTHROW type[n]
1874 # endif
1875 # ifndef SOAP_PLACEMENT_NEW
1876 # define SOAP_PLACEMENT_NEW(soap, buf, type) new (buf) (type)
1877 # endif
1878 #endif

1898 # define SOAP_MESSAGE fprintf
1899 # endif
1900 # ifndef DBGLOG
1901 # ifdef DEBUG_STAMP
1902 # ifdef WIN32
1903 # define DBGLOG(DBGFILE, CMD) \
1904 { if (soap)\
1905  { if (!soap->fdebug[SOAP_INDEX_##DBGFILE])\
1906  soap_open_logfile((struct soap*)soap, SOAP_INDEX_##DBGFILE);\
1907  if (soap->fdebug[SOAP_INDEX_##DBGFILE])\
1908  { FILE *fdebug = soap->fdebug[SOAP_INDEX_##DBGFILE];\
1909  SYSTEMTIME _localTime;\
1910  ::GetLocalTime(&_localTime); \
1911  fprintf(fdebug, "%02d%02d%02d %02d:%02d:%02d.%03d|", (int)_localTime.wYear%100, (int)_localTime.wMonth, (int)_localTime.wDay, (int)_localTime.wHour, (int)_localTime.wMinute, (int)_localTime.wSecond, (int)_localTime.wMilliseconds);\
1912  CMD;\
1913  fflush(fdebug);\
1914  }\
1915  }\
1916 }
1917 # else
1918 # define DBGLOG(DBGFILE, CMD) \
1919 { if (soap)\
1920  { if (!soap->fdebug[SOAP_INDEX_##DBGFILE])\
1921  soap_open_logfile((struct soap*)soap, SOAP_INDEX_##DBGFILE);\
1922  if (soap->fdebug[SOAP_INDEX_##DBGFILE])\
1923  { FILE *fdebug = soap->fdebug[SOAP_INDEX_##DBGFILE];\
1924  struct timeval _tv;\
1925  struct tm _tm;\
1926  gettimeofday(&_tv, NULL);\
1927  localtime_r(&_tv.tv_sec, &_tm);\
1928  fprintf(fdebug, "%02d%02d%02d %02d:%02d:%02d.%06ld|", (int)_tm.tm_year%100, (int)_tm.tm_mon+1, (int)_tm.tm_mday, (int)_tm.tm_hour, (int)_tm.tm_min, (int)_tm.tm_sec, (long)_tv.tv_usec);\
1929  CMD;\
1930  fflush(fdebug);\
1931  }\
1932  }\
1933 }
1934 # endif
1935 # else
1936 # define DBGLOG(DBGFILE, CMD) \
1937 { if (soap)\
1938  { if (!soap->fdebug[SOAP_INDEX_##DBGFILE])\
1939  soap_open_logfile((struct soap*)soap, SOAP_INDEX_##DBGFILE);\
1940  if (soap->fdebug[SOAP_INDEX_##DBGFILE])\
1941  { FILE *fdebug = soap->fdebug[SOAP_INDEX_##DBGFILE];\
1942  CMD;\
1943  fflush(fdebug);\
1944  }\
1945  }\
1946 }
1947 # endif
1948 # endif
1949 # ifndef DBGMSG
1950 # define DBGMSG(DBGFILE, MSG, LEN) \
1951 { if (soap)\
1952  { if (!soap->fdebug[SOAP_INDEX_##DBGFILE])\
1953  soap_open_logfile((struct soap*)soap, SOAP_INDEX_##DBGFILE);\
1954  if (soap->fdebug[SOAP_INDEX_##DBGFILE])\
1955  { fwrite((void*)(MSG), 1, (size_t)(LEN), soap->fdebug[SOAP_INDEX_##DBGFILE]);\
1956  fflush(soap->fdebug[SOAP_INDEX_##DBGFILE]);\
1957  }\
1958  }\
1959 }
1960 # endif
1961 # ifndef DBGFUN
1962 # define DBGFUN(FNAME) DBGLOG(TEST, SOAP_MESSAGE(fdebug, "%s(%d): %s()\n", __FILE__, __LINE__, FNAME))
1963 # define DBGFUN1(FNAME, FMT, ARG) DBGLOG(TEST, SOAP_MESSAGE(fdebug, "%s(%d): %s(" FMT ")\n", __FILE__, __LINE__, FNAME, (ARG)))
1964 # define DBGFUN2(FNAME, FMT1, ARG1, FMT2, ARG2) DBGLOG(TEST, SOAP_MESSAGE(fdebug, "%s(%d): %s(" FMT1 ", " FMT2 ")\n", __FILE__, __LINE__, FNAME, (ARG1), (ARG2)))
1965 # define DBGFUN3(FNAME, FMT1, ARG1, FMT2, ARG2, FMT3, ARG3) DBGLOG(TEST, SOAP_MESSAGE(fdebug, "%s(%d): %s(" FMT1 ", " FMT2 ", " FMT3 ")\n", __FILE__, __LINE__, FNAME, (ARG1), (ARG2), (ARG3)))
1966 # define DBGFUN4(FNAME, FMT1, ARG1, FMT2, ARG2, FMT3, ARG3, FMT4, ARG4) DBGLOG(TEST, SOAP_MESSAGE(fdebug, "%s(%d): %s(" FMT1 ", " FMT2 ", " FMT3 ", " FMT4 ")\n", __FILE__, __LINE__, FNAME, (ARG1), (ARG2), (ARG3), (ARG4)))
1967 # endif
1968 # ifndef DBGHEX
1969 # define DBGHEX(DBGFILE, MSG, LEN) \
1970 { if (soap)\
1971  { if (!soap->fdebug[SOAP_INDEX_##DBGFILE])\
1972  soap_open_logfile(soap, SOAP_INDEX_##DBGFILE);\
1973  if (soap->fdebug[SOAP_INDEX_##DBGFILE])\
1974  { int i; char *s;\
1975  for (s = (char*)(MSG), i = (LEN); i; i--)\
1976  fprintf(soap->fdebug[SOAP_INDEX_##DBGFILE], "%2.2X ", (int)*s++&0xFF);\
1977  fflush(soap->fdebug[SOAP_INDEX_##DBGFILE]);\
1978  }\
1979  }\
1980 }
1981 # endif
1982 #else
1983 # define DBGLOG(DBGFILE, CMD)
1984 # define DBGMSG(DBGFILE, MSG, LEN)
1985 # define DBGFUN(FNAME)
1986 # define DBGFUN1(FNAME, FMT, ARG)
1987 # define DBGFUN2(FNAME, FMT1, ARG1, FMT2, ARG2)
1988 # define DBGFUN3(FNAME, FMT1, ARG1, FMT2, ARG2, FMT3, ARG3)
1989 # define DBGFUN4(FNAME, FMT1, ARG1, FMT2, ARG2, FMT3, ARG3, FMT4, ARG4)
1990 # define DBGHEX(DBGFILE, MSG, LEN)
1991 #endif

2116  { return (bool)(content == iter.content); }
2117  bool operator!=(const soap_multipart_iterator& iter) const
2118  { return (bool)(content != iter.content); }
2119  struct soap_multipart& operator*() const
2120  { return *content; }
2121  struct soap_multipart *operator->() const
2122  { return content; }
2123  soap_multipart_iterator& operator++()
2124  { content = soap_next_multipart(content); return *this; }
2125  soap_multipart_iterator operator++(int)
2126  { soap_multipart_iterator iter(*this); content = soap_next_multipart(content); return iter; }
2127  soap_multipart_iterator() : content(NULL)
2128  { }
2129  soap_multipart_iterator(struct soap_multipart *p) : content(p)

3634 /* C++ templates (for generated C++ only, not needed nor used in generated C code) */
3635 
3636 template<class T>
3637 struct soap_block
3638 {
3639  static T *push(struct soap *soap, struct soap_blist *b)
3640  {
3641  if (!b)
3642  b = soap->blist;
3643  if (!b)
3644  return NULL;
3645  T *p = (T*)soap_push_block_max(soap, b, sizeof(T));
3646  if (p)
3647  SOAP_PLACEMENT_NEW(soap, p, T);
3648  return p;
3649  }
3650  static void pop(struct soap *soap, struct soap_blist *b)
3651  {
3652  if (!b)
3653  b = soap->blist;
3654  if (!b || !b->head)
3655  return;
3656  ((T*)(b->head + 1))->~T();
3657  soap_pop_block(soap, b);
3658  }
3659  static void save(struct soap *soap, struct soap_blist *b, T *p)
3660  {
3661  if (!b)
3662  b = soap->blist;
3663  for (T *q = (T*)soap_first_block(soap, b); q; q = (T*)soap_next_block(soap, b))
3664  {
3665  soap_update_pointers(soap, (const char*)p, (const char*)q, sizeof(T));
3666  *p++ = *q;
3667  q->~T();
3668  }
3669  soap_end_block(soap, b);
3670  }
3671  static void end(struct soap *soap, struct soap_blist *b)
3672  {
3673  if (!b)
3674  b = soap->blist;
3675  for (T *p = (T*)soap_first_block(soap, b); p; p = (T*)soap_next_block(soap, b))
3676  p->~T();
3677  soap_end_block(soap, b);
3678  }
3679 };
3680 
3681 #endif
3682 
3683 #endif /* STDSOAP_H */
